		<!-- Manual Transcriptions -->
		<!-- Sick ’Em, Back to Baltimore, Phil and His 4d, Tour No. 2, The Poor Simp, Where Do You Get That Noise?, Oh You Bonehead!, Good for the Soul -->
		<!-- A One-Man Team, Tour Y-10, The Holdout, Ball-a-Hole, Gas Oil and Air, The Yellow Kid, The Last Night, The Battle of the Century, Bedtime Stories -->
		<!-- A Closeup of Domba Splew, What of It? -->
		<dc:source>https://github.com/homestar92/ring-lardner-transcriptions</dc:source>
		<meta property="se:production-notes">"The Clubby Roadster" had very poor quality scans. One illegible word was filled in with context clues and an educated guess. In dialect-heavy works, the spelling errors were preserved if they were likely to be intentional based on ngrams and other Lardner stories of the era.</meta>
